OL,5, A magistrate has said he quit after    
OL,6, being left unable to check vulnerable  
OL,7, people were being protected when energy
OL,8, firms sought warrants to force-fit     
OL,9, prepayment meters.                     
OL,11,FRobin Cantrill-Fenwick said changes to 
OL,12,Fthe court system meant magistrates     
OL,13,F"were doing nothing more than rubber   
OL,14,Fstamping" warrants.                    
OL,16,FHe said the lack of scrutiny is putting
OL,17,Fvulnerable households at risk.         
OL,19,FOfgem has told suppliers to suspend    
OL,20,Fforce-fitting pay-as-you-go meters.    
